properties.name: Community Information
properties.webBody:
This message is being issued for Diamond Creek.
  • There is a house fire on Fairview Crescent.
  • Firefighters are currently responding to this fire. Keep the area clear for them.
  • Smoke may be visible from nearby roads and communities.
There is no immediate threat to the community and no action is required.
This message was issued by Country Fire Authority.

Unless the situation changes, this will be the last message issued for this fire.   

Health information: 
  • If you need medical advice for exposure to smoke, seek medical advice or call Nurse on Call on 1300 606 024. 
  • Anyone experiencing wheezing, chest tightness and difficulty breathing should call Triple Zero (000).     
Use multiple sources to stay informed: 
  • www.emergency.vic.gov.au 
  • VicEmergency Hotline - freecall 1800 226 226 
  • VicEmergency app 
  • Facebook or Twitter 
  • Tune in to ABC Local Radio, commercial and designated community radio stations, or Sky News TV. 
Accessibility: 
The following services can help you, or someone you know, access information during an emergency. 
  • To access this information in other languages, call the Translating and Interpreting Service on 131 450 (freecall) and ask them to call VicEmergency Hotline.
  • If you are deaf, hard of hearing, or have a speech/communication impairment contact National Relay Service on 1800 555 677 and ask them to call the VicEmergency Hotline.

properties.name: Advice
properties.location: Corringle, Newmerella, Simpsons Creek, Waygara, Bete Bolong, Marlo, Orbost
properties.webBody:
This Advice message is being issued for Bete Bolong, Corringle, Marlo, Newmerella, Orbost, Simpsons Creek, Waygara.

  • There is a grassfire at Princes Hwy, Simpsons Creek that is not yet under control.
  • Fire and smoke is visible on both sides of the Highway. 
  • A containment line has been constructed and firefighters will be actively patrolling today due to the forecasted winds
  • This Advice message replaces the Advice issued at 9:28pm Tuesday 19 September. 
There is currently no threat to you, but you should stay informed and monitor conditions.
What you should do: 
  • Keep the roads clear so emergency services can respond.
Impacts in your area: 
  • Visit https://traffic.vicroads.vic.gov.au/ for traffic impacts to the Princes Highway. 
  • Smoke will be visible from nearby communities and roads. 
This message was issued by Country Fire Authority.

The next update is expected by 20/09/2023 01:30 pm or as the situation changes.

Use multiple sources to stay informed: 
  • www.emergency.vic.gov.au
  • VicEmergency Hotline - freecall 1800 226 226
  • VicEmergency app
  • Facebook or Twitter (#vicfires)
  • Tune in to ABC Local Radio, commercial and designated community radio stations, or Sky News TV.
Accessibility:
The following services can help you, or someone you know, access information during an emergency.
  • To access this information in other languages call the Translating and Interpreting Service on 131 450 (freecall) and ask them to call VicEmergency Hotline.
  • If you are deaf, hard of hearing, or have a speech/communication impairment contact National Relay Service on 1800 555 677 and ask them to call the VicEmergency Hotline.

properties.name: Severe Weather Warning for DAMAGING WINDS
properties.webHeadline:
DAMAGING WINDS, averaging 60 to 70 km/h with peak gusts of around 100 km/h are likely about elevated parts of the warning area Wednesday morning.

Winds are expected to ease below warning thresholds from early Wednesday afternoon.


Locations which may be affected include Dargo, Falls Creek, Mt Hotha...
